0for%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20world%20leaders%20had%20flown%20in%20and%20the%20Centre's%20bureaucratic%20machinery%20was%20working%20overtime%20to%20ensure%20a%20perfect%20show.%20But%20the%20summit's%20success%20depended%20on%20one%20question%3A%20will%20there%20be%20consensus%20in%20the%20Leaders'%20Declaration%3F%20And%20it%20is%20this%20question%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20asked%20Sherpa%20Amitabh%20Kant%20an%20hour%20before%20the%20summit%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20has%20narrated%20this%20key%20exchange%20with%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20September%209%2C%202023%20in%20his%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20India%20Scaled%20Mt%20G20%3A%20The%20Inside%20Story%20of%20the%20G20%20Presidency%26quot%3B%20(Rupa%20Publications).%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20reached%20Bharat%20Mandapam%20to%20review%20the%20preparations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20to%20brief%20him%20on%20our%20progress%20so%20far.%20When%20he%20enquired%20about%20the%20Leaders'%20Declaration%2C%20I%20outlined%20the%20conflict%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20and%20informed%20him%20that%20the%20NDLD%20(New%20Delhi%20Leaders'%20Declaration)%20was%20still%20not%20finalised%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%20in%20his%20book%2C%20news%20agency%20PTI%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20paused%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20wondering%20as%20to%20why%20bilateral%20issues%20were%20being%20raised%20in%20a%20multilateral%20meeting%2C%20before%20replying%20that%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20get%20into%20the%20procedures%20or%20the%20process%2C%20but%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20result%20-%20a%20consensus%20-%20very%20soon.%20He%20expected%20the%20Sherpa%20to%20navigate%20and%20secure%20the%20final%20agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20details%20the%20gruelling%20work%20that%20made%20summit%20a%20success.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20had%20announced%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%2037-page%20declaration%20and%20its%20subsequent%20adoption%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20second%20session%20on%20the%20opening%20day%20of%20the%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20has%20detailed%20in%20his%20book%20how%20New%20Delhi%20managed%20to%20navigate%20geopolitical%20currents%20and%20bilateral%20issues%20to%20reach%20this%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20text%20continued%20to%20face%20constant%20revisions%20and%20objections%20after%20300%20hours%20of%20negotiations%20over%20250%20bilateral%20meetings.%20The%20weight%20and%20seriousness%20of%20the%20negotiations%20were%20felt%20by%20all%20participants%2C%20but%20the%20pursuit%20of%20a%20mutually%20agreeable%20outcome%20still%20seemed%20far%20from%20reach%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20writes%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bacutely%20aware%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20stakes%20involved%20and%20had%20asked%20for%20regular%20briefings.%20%26quot%3BHe%20had%20asked%20me%20to%20send%20him%20urgent%20situation%20reports%20every%20two%20hours%2C%20a%20task%20that%20demanded%20immense%20multitasking%20and%20quick%20analysis.%20This%20constant%20communication%20kept%20PM%20Modi%20informed%2C%20but%20also%20spurred%20us%20into%20action%2C%20helping%20us%20map%20out%20the%20negotiations%20and%20take%20stock%20of%20our%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20writes%20that%20Russia%20had%20insisted%20that%20the%20word%20'sanction'%20be%20included%20in%20the%20declaration.%20Extensive%20discussions%20were%20held%20with%20Alexander%20Pankin%2C%20Russia's%20Deputy%20Minister%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%2C%20to%20persuade%20them%20to%20reconsider%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stakes%20were%20high%2C%20as%20refusal%20to%20compromise%20would%20have%20left%20Russia%20isolated%20with%20a%2019-1%20vote%20against%20it.%20We%20finally%20had%20to%20tell%20Russia%20that%20this%20was%20not%20feasible%20and%20would%20not%20be%20accepted%20by%20other%20countries.%20We%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20to%20Russia%20that%20its%20insistence%20on%20this%20matter%20put%20significant%20pressure%20on%20India%20and%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20us%20to%20move%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20Sherpa%20has%20said%20that%20throughout%20the%20negotiations%2C%20G7%20countries%20--%20Canada%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Italy%2C%20Japan%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%20--%20pressured%20India%20to%20invite%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%2C%20but%20India's%20stance%20was%20to%20restrict%20the%20guest%20list%20to%20G20%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20Dr%20Jaishankar's%20advice%2C%20I%20had%20to%20inform%20the%20Russian%20negotiator%20that%20if%20they%20didn't%20agree%2C%20the%20first%20speaker%20following%20PM%20Modi's%20speech%20would%20be%20Zelenskyy.%20This%20bold%20and%20assertive%20negotiation%20tactic%20ultimately%20worked%2C%20and%20Russia%20relented%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20another%20hurdle.%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%20that%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Chinese%20team%20pointed%20out%20a%20bilateral%20challenge%20with%20the%20US%2C%20stemming%20from%20a%20part%20of%20the%20declaration%20that%20stated%20that%20the%202026%20G20%20Summit%20would%20be%20hosted%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Sherpa%2C%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%2C%20explained%20that%20the%20US%20would%20not%20grant%20them%20visas%2C%20not%20even%20for%20their%20governor%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%20They%20would%20not%20agree%20to%20the%20geopolitical%20paras%20until%20they%20received%20a%20written%20guarantee%20that%20they%20would%20be%20issued%20visas%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leaders'%20meeting%20started%20at%209%20am%20and%20Mr%20Kant%20held%20parallel%20negotiations%20from%209.30%20am%20to%2011.30%20am%20in%20a%20room%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Leaders'%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%2C%20along%2