0Kristianne%20who%20is%20one%20year%20older%2C%20and%20another%20sister%2C%20Libby%2C%20who%20is%20nine%20years%20younger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-17-surprising-facts-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGates'%20childhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20fostered%20his%20love%20of%20technology.%20He%20largely%20eschewed%20sports%20and%20more%20typical%20childhood%20activities%2C%20instead%20taking%20an%20early%20interest%20in%20technology.%20He%20wrote%20his%20first%20lines%20of%20code%20while%20still%20a%20young%20teen%3B%20it%20was%20a%20software%20program%20that%20allowed%20a%20human%20to%20face%20off%20against%20a%20computer%20playing%20tic-tac-toe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222036%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20grainy%20black%20and%20white%20photo%20shows%20a%20young%20Bill%20Gates%20in%201984.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5220f9776bb3f7222a8b4599%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Gates%20was%20a%20computer%20whiz%20from%20an%20early%20age%2C%20and%20later%20dropped%20out%20of%20Harvard%20and%20went%20on%20to%20found%20Microsoft.%3Cp%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Bill%20Gates%20was%20in%20high%20school%20at%20Lakeside%20Prep%20School%2C%20he%20was%20writing%20code%20for%20the%20school%20itself%20and%20was%20soon%20working%20with%20the%20Computer%20Center%20Corporation%2C%20a%20local%20business%20in%20Seattle%20that%20offered%20users%20time%20on%20their%20computers%2C%20personal%20computers%20still%20being%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20future.%20(Gates%20was%20briefly%20banned%20from%20the%20CCC%20for%20sneaking%20in%20lines%20of%20code%20that%20granted%20him%20extended%20free%20time%20using%20the%20machines.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBill%20Gates%20would%20go%20on%20to%20matriculate%20at%20Harvard%20University%20in%20the%20fall%20of%201973%2C%20but%20he%20would%20not%20finish%20his%20college%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248ffefac-31f6-4cc2-bcb4-a451f5c59aef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20foundation%20and%20growth%20of%20Microsoft%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20of%201975%2C%20Gates%20and%20fellow%20software%20genius%20and%20childhood%20friend%20Paul%20Allen%20moved%20to%20Albuquerque%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20to%20work%20for%20the%20company%20Micro%20Instrumentation%20and%20Telemetry%20Systems%2C%20Inc.%20(MITS)%2C%20a%20company%20that%20was%20just%20beginning%20to%20create%20PCs%20(personal%20computers).%20Gates%20managed%20to%20convince%20the%20executives%20he%20and%20Allen%20could%20create%20software%20for%20their%20new%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20role%20did%20not%20last%20long.%20Later%20that%20same%20year%2C%20Gates%20and%20Allen%20founded%20their%20own%20company%2C%20named%20for%20%26quot%3Bmicrocomputer%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsoftware%2C%26quot%3B%20known%20today%20as%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20Bill%20Gates%20and%20Paul%20Allen%20lean%20against%20a%20desk%20in%20a%201970s%20office.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671ff1d001ea6d83dee4980a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGates%20and%20his%20longtime%20friend%20Paul%20Allen%20founded%20Microsoft%20together%20and%20launched%20the%20massively%20successful%20Windows%20operating%20system%20just%20a%20few%20years%20later.%3Cp%3EDoug%20Wilson%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20relocated%20to%20Bellevue%2C%20Washington%2C%20in%201979%2C%20and%20in%201980%2C%20the%20company%20made%20a%20deal%20with%20tech%20juggernaut%20IBM%20to%20develop%20an%20operating%20system%20for%20the%20company's%20first%20consumer-ready%20PC.%20The%20MS-DOS%201.0%20OS%20was%20released%20in%20the%20summer%20of%20the%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20just%20four%20years%20later%2C%20in%201985%2C%20Microsoft%20released%20the%20first%20version%20of%20its%20now%20vaunted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-mark-zuckerberg-elon-musk-lesson-of-microsoft-windows-platforms-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWindows%20OS%3C%2Fa%3E.%20New%20versions%20of%20Windows%20would%20come%20out%20every%20few%20years%20from%20that%20point%20on%2C%20and%20it%20has%20grown%20so%20dominant%20that%20nearly%20three-quarters%20of%20the%20world's%20computers%20run%20Windows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20departed%20from%20Microsoft%20for%20medical%20reasons%20in%201983%20(though%20he%20would%20live%20another%20quarter%20of%20a%20century)%2C%20while%20Gates%20would%20remain%20the%20CEO%20until%20the%20summer%20of%202008%2C%20when%20he%20voluntarily%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20leading%20role%20of%20the%20company%20he%20had%20grown%20into%20a%20company%20that%20would%20enjoy%20revenues%20of%20more%20than%20%2460%20billion%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2210f76eac-e2d0-4f67-95a2-d8b7b3b343fd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGates'%20post-Microsoft%20career%20and%20philanthropy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Gates%20stepped%20down%20as%20CEO%20of%20Microsoft%2C%20he%20stepped%20up%20as%20the%20co-founder%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-and-melinda-gates-foundation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20charitable%20organization%20he%20and%20his%20then%20wife%20Melinda%20Gates%20had%20founded%20in%20the%20year%202000.%20(The%20foundation%20was%20a%20revamp%20of%20the%20organization%20Gates%20had%20established%20in%201994%20under%20the%20name%20the%20William%20H.%20Gates%20Foundation.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BMFG%20is%20a%20nonprofit%20with%20global%20reach%20that%20happens%20to%20make%20a%20tidy%20profit%2C%20thanks%20in%20no%20small%20part%20to%20its%20massive%20holdings%20of%20Microsoft%20st