societal%20and%20economic%20factors%20working%20against%20them%2C%20high-earning%20single%20women%20understand%20that%20building%20equity%20through%20owning%20a%20home%20will%20help%20set%20them%20up%20for%20longer-term%20financial%20stability%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20second%20income%20stream%20from%20a%20partner%20or%20spouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20look%20at%20this%20by%20race%2C%20by%20age%2C%20by%20generation%2C%20we%20see%20the%20same%20trend.%20Women%20just%20outperform%20on%20homeownership.%20And%20this%20is%20something%20that%20we've%20seen%20consistently%20in%20the%20data%20since%20we%20started%20tracking%20it%20in%201981%2C%26quot%3B%20NAR's%20chief%20economist%20Jessica%20Lautz%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20something%20that's%20been%20important%20for%20generations%20of%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20women%20still%20face%20outsize%20challenges%20when%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20sacrifice%20they%20appear%20increasingly%20willing%20to%20make%2C%20Lautz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20settle%20for%20a%20smaller%20space%20or%20wait%20until%20they%20are%20older%20to%20buy%20than%20single%20men%2C%20with%20a%20median%20age%20for%20first-time%20buyers%20of%2038%20compared%20to%2033%20for%20men%2C%20according%20to%20NAR%20data%20for%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingle%20women%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20move%20in%20with%20friends%20or%20family%20before%20purchasing%20to%20avoid%20paying%20rent%2C%20helping%20save%20up%20for%20longer.%20That%20was%20the%20case%20for%20Meghan%2C%20who%20told%20BI%20she%20moved%20in%20with%20her%20mom%20for%20a%20year%20after%20graduating%20from%20nursing%20school%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20really%20started%20to%20fall%20into%20place%2C%20though%2C%20when%20she%20got%20a%20boost%20to%20her%20travel%20nurse%20salary%20as%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20drew%20huge%20demand%20for%20nurses%20around%20the%20country.%20This%20helped%20her%20save%20up%20for%20a%20down%20payment%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year-old%20made%20the%20jump%20to%20homeownership%20in%20December%202022%20with%20help%20from%20a%20state-funded%20program%20for%20first-time%20buyers%20that%20she%20used%20to%20buy%20a%20575-square-foot%20condo%20in%20Boston.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20moving%20in%2C%20she%20struggled%20a%20bit%20to%20make%20her%20monthly%20%242%2C400%20mortgage%20payment%20as%20she%20split%20her%20time%20between%20working%20and%20finishing%20her%20nurse%20practitioner's%20degree%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20decision%20she%20felt%20confident%20in%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20skin%20of%20my%20teeth%2C%20I%20made%20it%20through%20a%20really%20tough%20year.%20My%20savings%20were%20already%20depleted%20from%20buying%20the%20house%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20it%20got%20easier%20after%20her%20salary%20increased%20again%20with%20her%20new%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Meghan%2C%20many%20women%20have%20increasingly%20pursued%20higher%20education%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20another%20area%20where%20they've%20outpaced%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20be%20another%20driver%20of%20their%20higher%20homeownership%20rates%2C%20First%20American's%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20Odeta%20Kushi%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20these%20things%E2%80%94educational%20attainment%2C%20household%20income%20for%20women%E2%80%94continue%20to%20rise%2C%20it's%20pretty%20reasonable%20to%20expect%20increased%20homeownership%20rate%20to%20follow%20suit.%20It's%20increasingly%20pursuing%20homeownership%2C%20and%20reaping%20its%20wealth%20creation%20benefits%20for%20this%20group%2C%26quot%3B%20Kushi%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFemale%20homebuyers%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20prioritize%20stability%2C%20Lautz%20said%2C%20making%20the%20certainty%20of%20a%2030-year%20mortgage%20especially%20attractive%20as%20rental%20prices%20shoot%20through%20the%20roof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Julia%20Donnelly%2C%20the%20switch%20from%20a%20rental%20in%20Boston%20to%20a%20home%20closer%20to%20her%20family%20in%20the%20suburbs%20last%20year%20was%20a%20no-brainer%20as%20she%20saw%20her%20savings%20diminish%20with%20each%20rental%20payment%20she%20owed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20worked%20in%20the%20Boston%20area%20as%20well%20as%20New%20York%20and%20New%20Jersey%2C%20so%20obviously%20renting%20in%20those%20three%20cities%20means%20pretty%20high%20rental%20costs%20that%20continue%20to%20rise%20each%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2034-year-old%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20keep%20trading%20away%20all%20my%20money%20on%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20rise%20in%20single%20female%20homeownership%2C%20too%2C%20could%20be%20that%20Americans%20in%20general%20are%20holding%20out%20longer%20to%20get%20married%2C%20Kushi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20the%20nursery%20rhyme%2C%20'first%20comes%20love%2C%20then%20comes%20marriage.'%20And%20I%20feel%20like%20for%20single%20women%2C%20first%20comes%20home%20ownership%2C%26quot%3B%20Kushi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Donnelly%2C%20it%20didn't%20make%20sense%20to%20put%20her%20financial%20goals%20on%20pause%20while%20waiting%20to%20find%20a%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20find%20the%20right%20person%2C%20I%20might%20be%20already%20set%20up%20to%20get%20life%20rolling.%20If%20not%2C%20I%20have%20a%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Donnelly%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20a%20little%20more%20control%20rather%20than%20waiting%20for%20someone%20else%20to%20come%20along%20to%20make%20life%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20Meghan%2C%20see%20their%20homes%20as%20a%20lasting%20investment%20as%20prices%20continue%20to%20climb%2C%20even%20if%20she%20may%20want%20to%20eventually%20upgrade%20to%20a%20larger%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I'll%20ever%20sell%20it.%20If%20anything%2C%20I'd%20just%20have%20someone%20move%20in%2C%20or%20I'd%20just%20keep%20it%20and%20rent%20it.%20I%20think%20owning%20property%2C%20especially%20in%20Boston%2C%20is%20invaluable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20women's%20respective%20homes%20have%20proved%20to%20be%20everything%20they%20wanted%2C%20with%20the%20security%20of%20calling%20it%20their%20own%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20it's%20helping%20them%20feel%20more%20independent%20and%20confident%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20all%20these%20things%20where%20I'm%20like%2C%20'Oh%20man%2C%20I'm%20way%20more%20capable%20than%20I%20thought%20I%20was%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Megan%20O'Neil%2C%20a%2036-year-old%20who%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20Memphis%20back%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20changed%20her%20outlook%20on%20dating%2C%20too%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20might%20be%20very%20intimidating%20to%20some%20guys%2C%20but%20I%20need%20a%20partner.%20I%20don't%20need%20somebody%20to%20take%20care%20of%20me.%20I%20need%20a%20partner%2C%20because%20I%20can%20do%20this%20by%20myself%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-women-first-time-homebuyers-housing-market-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736674202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e341a6cfb7f307e5711fd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-women-first-time-homebuyers-housing-market-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20a%20gender%20wage%20gap%20and%20high%20home%20prices%2C%20single%20women%20are%20outperforming%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kcloonan%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Cloonan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-women-first-time-hom